### 2. [secureStorage.ts](file:///c:/Users/ajmal_inv2bct/OneDrive/Desktop/web%20projects/spirox/apps/web/src/lib/secureStorage.ts) (NEW)

A drop-in encrypted wrapper for `localStorage`.

| Method | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `setItem(key, value)` | Encrypts value → writes `enc::` + base64 ciphertext |
| `getItem(key)` | Reads → detects `enc::` prefix → decrypts → returns plaintext |
| `migrateKey(key)` | Reads plain-text value → re-encrypts in place |
| `migrateAll(keys)` | Batch-migrates multiple keys (idempotent) |

Key design decisions:
- **Legacy compatibility**: Values without the `enc::` prefix are returned as-is (supports gradual migration from existing plain-text data).
- **Tamper detection**: If decryption fails (data was edited in DevTools), the corrupted key is removed and `null` is returned.
- **SSR safety**: Falls back gracefully when `crypto.subtle` is unavailable (server-side rendering).

